Hot take: NCT should have been doing this type of rollout since the beginning.  

NCT U has great songs and the opportunities for different members to be highlighted.  It also lets members hold positions they usually don’t have the opportunity to be in.  

Every song in this rollout has been way better than usual as well.  I was personally getting a little tired of hearing the same formula and seeing the same members do the same things.

author: @pppp__67
text:
Why is Haechan and Taeyong cut out during the last chorus view of this MV? If there are members spread out in the position and it’s a verse supposedly for everyone, why is the camera not panning to them? Aren’t they supposed to be in frame as well? Why is Haechan’s high note not emphasized even for a short while? I get that it was a dance choreo for everyone but why was it not given importance but Jaehyun’s whistle was shown? What was the reason? 

Until now it’s still baffling as to how these things keep happening to certain members of the group that is supposed to highlight EVERYBODY. To think that this is NCT U, a new combination or set of members together, yet, treatment such as these are still apparent. Such a shame. 

Haechan and Taeyong deserves so much better.

Additional: SM should take note of the impact Haechan and Taeyong has brought for the company, especially with PADO’s performance last NCT Nation Concert where Haechan trended for FOUR (4) days  straight. It was the only song (aside from Golden Age) he participated in their latest group album ‘Golden Age’ and yet look at his demand. SM is missing out big time with suppressing and putting Haechan in the basement when he’s an all-rounder and can do so much as an artist. Really so much of a shame.
